<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8010&amp;p=34622#p34622"><![CDATA[
I refer to the initial and a follow up posting generated by John Gray and to the response offered by Gaurav.<br /><br />I am not knowledgeable about the internal operation of Windows 10 but I respectfully ask the developers of Classic Shell to reconsider their future participation in offering and extending the life of ClassicShell so as the provide an alternative to Windows 10 so called start menu and tile menu system.<br /><br />I have just installed windows 10 1709 (after waiting 4 months for the upgraded contents to be serviceable) and after arranging the customization of the existing ClassicShell (4.3.1 installed within version 1703, I am now experiencing the same issues exactly as John Gray has reported.<br /><br />I believe that there is something in excess if <strong>13 million users around the world </strong>who have downloaded and probably installed ClassicShell over recent times and also probably effectively from the introduction of windows 10,<br /><br />So far there are two users (John and myself) who have reported the same issues with the Desktop refreshing every 4 or 5 seconds with little ability to stop the refreshing - there must be heaps more users who have the same issues experienced within this forum discussion.<br /><br />Is there any chance to learn that 'refreshing' repair could be made and that future servicing will be attended to look after Windows 10 inadequacies be made to ClassicShell so as to meet the shortfalls of Windows 10 start system by repairing version 4.3.1 and later versions of ClassicShell so that faults associated by Windows 10 will be built into ClassicShell.<br /><br />I plead - Help those of us who live by ClassicShell.... please?<br /><br />Regards to you all<br /><br />Kim<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=19429">Kimbo No1</a> — Tue Oct 31, 2017 12:31 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
